One person has been critically wounded in a shooting on the corner of Rivonia &amp; 11th Avenue in Sandton. JOHANNESBURG - One person has been critically wounded in a shooting on the corner of Rivonia and 11th Avenue in Sandton. Its understood the man was shot in the head, during a botched robbery outside the Rivonia Primary School this afternoon. He's been rushed to hospital. ER24's Russel Meiring says, The man sustained a serious gunshot wound and is in a critical condition. The man was immediately treated for his injuries and provided with advanced life support intervention. Once treated, he was transported to a nearby private hospital for urgent care.